content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and provide a detailed solution.

Main Target Image Analysis:
- The structure appears to be a tunnel or archway design
- It consists of multiple layers and different colored blocks (red, yellow, and orange)
- The structure has a base, middle section with a circular opening, and a roof portion
- There are approximately 9-10 blocks total

Layer Analysis:
1. Base layer: Red tunnel pieces and orange ramps
2. Middle layer: Red blocks forming circular opening
3. Top layer: Yellow curved pieces and orange triangular roof pieces

Required Blocks and Assembly Order:
{
Step1: Move block with index 1 (red arch base)
Step2: Move block with index 2 (red U-shaped piece, left side)
Step3: Move block with index 3 (red U-shaped piece, right side)
Step4: Move block with index 6 (yellow curved piece, left)
Step5: Move block with index 7 (yellow curved piece, right)
Step6: Move block with index 13 (orange triangular ramp, left)
Step7: Move block with index 15 (orange triangular ramp, right)
Step8: Move block with index 12 (orange triangular roof piece, front)
Step9: Move block with index 12 (orange triangular roof piece, back)
}

The construction follows a bottom-up approach, starting with the base tunnel piece, adding the side supports, then the yellow curved decorative elements, and finally the orange triangular pieces to complete the roof structure.
